                    <p>We collect donated bicycles, make repairs and distribute them to students. In the summer of 2014 we loaned about 150 bicycles. Students who use our bikes are required to take a DelDOT safety class and take a group ride with the Rehoboth police to learn the area. We equip all bikes with the required front and rear lights, and offer every student a free helmet. During the summer we make house calls to repair any bike a student uses, whether loaned by us or acquired elsewhere. We also repair bikes while the students attend the free dinners offered by ISOP throughout the summer. All repairs, including those requiring parts, are free. If a bike can't be repaired, we will try to replace it.</p>
